<subSubSection id="3976DC1BB82870225B4B2055ED846C92" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="56EABE6FFF10DE183796299264213179" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="A8A5CAF6FB9BA5C31BF20D4D2A1AD708" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann and Eigenmann</taxonomicName>
, 1889 currently includes 18 species distributed chiefly in the coastal basins of southern and southeastern Brazil. One species is known from the Amazon. Coastal rivers of southern Brazil, namely the rivers of Santa Catarina State, represent the richest area of 
<taxonomicName id="54FC2CEC070E1310615A51B33A9F0B2B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
species. The upper Uruguay River in Rio Grande do Sul and Santa Catarina States is inhabited by three species, 
<taxonomicName id="AB7455F7D675F871C0C003E9E39DD227" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:99E338BE-9583-479F-B619-C765DFDC2D99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys vestigipinnis Pereira &amp; Reis 1992:113" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vestigipinnis">H. vestigipinnis Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 1992, 
<taxonomicName id="98EA8149983EC818A79B175B27D3CD19" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E7EF37F0-239F-4981-B469-43D843BC635D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys eurycephalus Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:131" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eurycephalus">H. eurycephalus Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002, and 
<taxonomicName id="C6D18366E911A00613FF823C1CB86BE4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:47F4AFEB-34AA-4F33-BFA1-DB0E5D924D36" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys hystrix Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:134" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hystrix">H. hystrix Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002. In addition, a small area of endemism composed of the coastal rivers 
<normalizedToken id="2E61578FF8F4CA0DE136A819BD16AB7C" originalValue="Maquiné">Maquine</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="28D91BCD79B170ABADDFE3A1E9794196" originalValue="Três">Tres</normalizedToken>
Forquilhas, Mampituba and 
<normalizedToken id="45BA6CA72F7789D0C48940838F5256C1" originalValue="Araranguá">Ararangua</normalizedToken>
(Reis and Schaefer 1998; Reis and Cardoso 2001), is inhabited by three other species, 
<taxonomicName id="700C51753CD13881AFE4B67C2FE82FD9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7C448DE5-260D-452A-87D4-C5218DA57F23" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys nudulus Reis &amp; Pereira 1999:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nudulus">H. nudulus Reis and Pereira</taxonomicName>
, 1999, 
<taxonomicName id="2BA62A5B82CE2666635E767C400C67EA" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:813AB04B-07E1-438B-BC0D-23A19B891561" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys hypselurus Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:136" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypselurus">H. hypselurus Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002, and 
<taxonomicName id="F37B50EAAE7B963B215C1AFD19919B6D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E093B3DB-8AFD-4443-A7EF-EACF65C89B6C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys stomias Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:139" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stomias">H. stomias Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002. Finally, remaining coastal rivers of Santa Catarina State north of the 
<normalizedToken id="01E65C5CCC97301D87E1CC727780A5F0" originalValue="Araranguá">Ararangua</normalizedToken>
River basin are occupied by four additional species, 
<taxonomicName id="0C003A807C94C8C66CCEAAE3B61ED31C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calmoni">H. calmoni (Steindachner</taxonomicName>
, 1907), 
<taxonomicName id="B8F78E401BD4A4A772930DA44FAAA425" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FCB9BEA5-4787-456C-84C4-F2C1FF851950" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys steindachneri Miranda-Ribeiro 1918:107" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steindachneri">H. steindachneri Miranda Ribeiro</taxonomicName>
, 1918, 
<taxonomicName id="DE6B04D08232F7E77E6F6A3B4EE40A99" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F66EA7B4-B6F2-47F4-8CE4-63D44850D1B1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys splendens Bizerril 1995:117" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendens">H. splendens Bizerril</taxonomicName>
, 1995, and 
<taxonomicName id="CAC9928428C5A4457937F360B05B3996" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CE811509-1698-4110-8BEB-E98EA368F5B7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys azygolechis Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:129" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="azygolechis">H. azygolechis Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002. North of the above area is a geographic gap for 
<taxonomicName id="26B5C83ED3EF75DF03924126EB776E64" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
, and the 
<normalizedToken id="366CB29119B15FE206CA93471C4E516E" originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
do Sul River is the next area where species belonging to this genus are found: 
<taxonomicName id="8434F3785D377A0F4B177E97873BD0AA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gobio">
H. gobio (
<normalizedToken id="3CC807BD18BCC0387C7116916F369456" originalValue="Lüt-">Luetken</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, 1874) and 
<taxonomicName id="C6CDE8FB8E9DD49446E5E41877F76F29" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3E509329-8426-4CFF-98ED-F01FE6B5DBD0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys papillatus Pereira, Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa 2000:378" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="papillatus">H. papillatus Pereira et al.</taxonomicName>
, 2000. Coastal rivers in Rio de Janeiro State, the 
<normalizedToken id="5E497D4B3ABC45F5736D3A4B0CD26AD9" originalValue="Macaé">Macae</normalizedToken>
and Macacu Rivers, are inhabited by 
<taxonomicName id="BD2185919D2A1AEE2E53BA8B85665212" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F8B68095-FB15-48CB-833A-EF2818D575A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys garbei Ihering 1911:399" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="garbei">H. garbei Ihering</taxonomicName>
, 1911. Still further north, three species of 
<taxonomicName id="1995FB6E3706A2D3E00C189B00FED8C5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
are found in the upper 
<normalizedToken id="03C70FD8D2B3CDA241A26FEB31CAC3E8" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco River and nearby coastal rivers of Bahia: 
<taxonomicName id="EB3E3B4F70428BC8959CBB0290C7B18C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bahianus">H. bahianus (Gosline</taxonomicName>
, 1947), 
<taxonomicName id="557610C06F2AF6D82E6A3E10B37D6265" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9FC5F271-F80A-48BB-B0A2-965E0C06DA83" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys stephanus de Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa 1999:77" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stephanus">H. stephanus Oliveira and Oyakawa</taxonomicName>
, 1999, and 
<taxonomicName id="0E6FC405CE3E441BAB5AF59FBC78A5A9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:050F358A-27A1-4E2A-AD74-BB6322E2B5B1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys mutuca de Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa 1999:75" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mutuca">H. mutuca Oliveira and Oyakawa</taxonomicName>
, 1999, and in the tributaries of the upper Negro River in the Amazon, 
<taxonomicName id="DC3F950E9AECC203950B5A6E1F85485D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5CC24274-572A-40F3-B283-298AA06DAE46" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys regani Giltay 1936:6" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="regani">H. regani Giltay</taxonomicName>
, 1936. Type locality and distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="7EA790A4E8BD618E42680B6E32B4A8FF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E16591F3-187A-41C9-ABE1-EFEA74E08AE1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys cerosus Miranda-Ribeiro &amp; Miranda-Ribeiro 1951:xxxix" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cerosus">H. cerosus Miranda Ribeiro</taxonomicName>
, 1951 are not known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03B657E0EA188C7E2F242EDC4523D09B" pageNumber="2">
Pereira and Reis (2002) recently produced a revision of 
<taxonomicName id="BA61DF35034D497E2CBD9B8D3481323D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C562CF0DFEF2D17011B50BA6671C9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys Derijst</taxonomicName>
, 1996, describing five new species of the former and redescribing all previously known species. Of the 18 known species, 11 were described during the last ten years and additional undescribed species await formal description. During a survey of coastal rivers on southeastern Brazil one of these undescribed species was detected in the upper 
<normalizedToken id="C6CDA8BB5A16E704F518577DEA5DD33D" originalValue="Perequê-Açu">Pereque-Acu</normalizedToken>
River by the two first authors. Independently, the two last authors also found the same new species during ecological studies in coastal rivers of southeastern Rio de Janeiro State.
</paragraph>
